Part II - Final Project Presentation + Methods Publication

Final Deliverable:

  • The final deliverable consists of two components:

    • Presentation formatted in Google Slides as a published presentation

    • PDF Methods Paper formatted on Google Drive as a published document

  • The final project submission is simply a .txt file with the following three items:

    • Project Abstract (approx. 150 - 200 words)
    • Published link to Methods
    • Published link to Project Presentation Slides

  • Copy the following accessible and editable Google Document. Utilize it as the template for your .txt deliverable. This is the only document that needs to be uploaded to Canvas for the final project submission.

    • Methods Link + Presentation Link + Abstract .txt

Final Project Steps (extended) - also covered in Final Project Step Slides in Lecture 13:

  • Step #1:

    • Project Proposal (completed)

  • Step #2:

    • Develop Methodology

  • Step #3:

    • Conduct GIS analysis

  • Step #4:

    • Complete analysis | Derive quantitative results | Summarization | Conclusive findings

  • Step #5A:

    • Make back up of all data and analysis for future reference
    • Presentation Design | Methods Paper | Publish Documents | Canvas Upload

  • Step #5B - Slides:

    • Finish Slides- either finalize and import to Google Slides; or create slides from start to finish within Google Slides

  • Step #5C Methods:

    • Complete methods paper at Google Drive. Include the following subsections in the methods paper:

      • Abstract
      • Introduction
      • Methodology & Analysis
      • Results
      • Conclusion
      • Works Cited | Bibliography | Data Sources

  • Step #6 Publishing Links:

    • Project Links Develop. Utilizing Google Drive, create two (2) share and publish links - one for the methods paper, and one for the presentation:

      • First, ensure that File > Share is set to Anyone with the link can view:

      Step 1 Publishing Links - Open File to view status

      • Second, ensure that File > Publish to the web is set to Publish using the link option. The Publish link is the submission link, not the first File > Share link.

      Step 2 Publishing Links - Fully Publish the Link and Secure Correct Share Address

  • Step #7 Create and Upload to Canvas your_name_final_GIS_project.txt:

    • Download the following .txt document as .txt and fill in the empty sections for your project details. Upload the completed .txt as .txt (not .pdf or .doc) to the assignment location at CANVAS:

      • Project Paper Link + Presentation Link + Abstract .txt

    • Ensure that both Publish to the web links (one for methods paper, one for slide presentation) as well as copy >paste of the abstract text from the methods paper is included in the Project Paper Link + Presentation Link + Abstract .txt submission.

    • Submit completed (copied and filled with your own project details) Project Paper Link + Presentation Link + Abstract .txt to the assignment section at Canvas for the Final Project.
